#SemarangBisaDikonserkan - sepertinya, ini kali kedua W nonton Cholil bareng ERK setelah Pensaga 2011. Ini juga kali pertama W nonton konser tunggal dengan durasi yang cukup lama (dua sesi dengan total waktu sekitar dua jam). Selain ERK, ada orkestra, beberapa musisi lokal, dan perwakilan warga Kendeng. Asik dan seru, cuy. Ngga nyesel, deh ngeluarin uang buat nonton konser itu. Gaya panggung Cholil yang ramah dan sopan seperti: memenuhi permintaan penonton untuk mengeraskan volume suara gitar dan menyanyikan lagu Jalang (padahal dadakan), memperkenalkan semua pemain musik di panggung, dan melayani penonton yang meminta foto bersama. Dua sesi ini memang puas, cuy. Sesi awal diisi lagu-lagu dari Album Sinestesia. Sesi kedua berisi lagu-lagu dari album sebelumnya, lagu-lagu kebanggaan W waktu masih pake K750i di SMP dulu kek Cinta Melulu, Balerina, dan Kenakalan Remaja di Era Informatika. Dan...selain itu, W lebih milih foto bareng Hasief daripada dengan personil ERK yang lain. Secara...W iri sik ma Hasief. Doi bisa jadi jurnalis musik (pekerjaan idaman W waktu masih abege dulu), keliling tempat buat ikut tur, kenalan dan ketemu musisi-musisi dunia, bebas makan bagel-burger-steak-minuman berkarbonasi. Tapi...ya gimane, W kok nggak milih pekerjaan itu ye dulu. üòÇüòÇ #EfekRumahKaca #NoRegret

I don't know whether the crowd played the great role or they played the music at their best perform, but for me (and so many people), Sheila on 7 (SO7) has valuable songs and easy to sung. It makes the crowd and the atmosphere felt great. Until this time, no wonder why SO7 still has many fans. SO7 had won them. From the show, I just knew that SO7 has their own style on ending the perform: they ask for goodbye by leaving the stage one by one (whereas, I hoped the crowd said "We want more," and they came back to the stage, but it did not happen). The great songs for me are Kisah Klasik and Hari Bersamanya. It has values on friendship and love. See, SO7 can reach the values.

finally, Elephant Kind. what an interesting and interactive performance. no wonder they got the reward for the best new musician in 2015 from Jakartabeat. I agree. caption.text: #MBA (Marching Band Atma Jaya Yogyakarta), it might be more amazing if the duration of performance was longer. But, it was, a quietly stunning performance.

#opinion is not judgmental: I've watched Barasuara almost 4/5 times (I forgot) in Bali, Yogyakarta and Semarang. The first time I saw them while in Bali, I was amazed and made Barasuara one of my favorite bands for stage action and stunning choreography (especially Iga, when he jumped to the audience at the end of show). But, the last two shows in Semarang and last night at Tebing Breksi were not that good for me. When the show was in Semarang, I thought it was a tough day for Barasuara personnel (because I knew their busy schedule on the weekend), I felt Iga as front man and vocalist looked tired. I felt it, because the way Iga communicated with the audience was not interactive, and his face was not so exciting when playing a song. At that time I thought, maybe it was not my lucky day to see the impressive action performance of Barasuara and will be different on the other show. Evidently, it happened again last night. Barasuara started playing not with fast-paced songs (like Sendu Melagu and Hagia). I hoped, they kept the fast-paced songs at the end so that the audience's emotions increased maximally. As it turned out, I was wrong. I thought Barasuara (especially Iga) just played song at a time, without trying to improve the audience's emotions. I realized that the audience who comes to the music concert do not just want to listen the song (because they can use music player), the audience wants to get the atmosphere (including the crowd, sound, and the action of their own idol). The consistency of a good stage action for me is Gerald. As the audience, of course I do not understand the tension and stress of a band personnel who play a role to entertain the audience, especially for the portion of vocalist and bass player, or others so that I can said so. Fortunately, the feeling last night helped because the last two songs, Bahas Bahasa and Api & Lentera. I will not be skeptical and still hope, hopefully I get a show with an outstanding stage action from Barasuara for the next show. \m/
